==English==
===Etymology===
Italian, from ''[[mezzo]]'', half, and ''[[soprano]]'', soprano

===Noun===
'''mezzo-soprano''' (''plural'' '''mezzo-sopranos''')

# a [[voice]] or voice part [[intermediate]] in [[compass]] between [[soprano]] and [[contralto]]
# a person having such a voice

===Adjective===

'''mezzo-soprano''' (''no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')

# of, pertaining to, characteristic of, or suitable to a mezzo-soprano
#:''mezzo-soprano range''

